(75, 1, '2026-03-30 22:55:08', '2026-03-30 22:55:08', '<p data-start=\"297\" data-end=\"382\"><strong data-start=\"297\" data-end=\"382\">A complete toolkit of mathematics for physics, engineering, and science students.</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"384\" data-end=\"587\"><em data-start=\"384\" data-end=\"431\">Mathematical Methods in the Physical Sciences</em> by <span class=\"hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline\"><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Mary L. Boas</span></span> is a widely used textbook designed to help students build strong problem-solving skills in advanced mathematics.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"589\" data-end=\"853\">It covers essential topics such as linear algebra, differential equations, Fourier series, complex variables, and vector calculus—providing the mathematical foundation needed for higher-level physics and engineering courses.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"855\" data-end=\"1051\">The book focuses on understanding and applying methods rather than heavy proofs, making it ideal for science students who need practical mathematical tools.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr data-start=\"1053\" data-end=\"1056\" />\r\n\r\n<h3 data-section-id=\"1mdoose\" data-start=\"1058\" data-end=\"1076\">✨ Key Features</h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1077\" data-end=\"1285\">\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1icy6jr\" data-start=\"1077\" data-end=\"1135\">Covers <strong data-start=\"1086\" data-end=\"1133\">all major math topics for physical sciences</strong></li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"zzmbwg\" data-start=\"1136\" data-end=\"1187\">Emphasis on <strong data-start=\"1150\" data-end=\"1185\">problem-solving and application</strong></li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"ewsxm\" data-start=\"1188\" data-end=\"1234\">Includes <strong data-start=\"1199\" data-end=\"1232\">hundreds of practice problems</strong></li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"cwo1hu\" data-start=\"1235\" data-end=\"1285\">Clear explanations without overly heavy proofs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr data-start=\"1287\" data-end=\"1290\" />\r\n\r\n<h3 data-section-id=\"1tetnml\" data-start=\"1292\" data-end=\"1310\">🎯 Perfect for</h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1311\" data-end=\"1449\">\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1e6vgzv\" data-start=\"1311\" data-end=\"1347\">Physics and engineering students</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"idzgar\" data-start=\"1348\" data-end=\"1380\">Applied mathematics students</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1b70lhw\" data-start=\"1381\" data-end=\"1449\">Anyone taking <strong data-start=\"1397\" data-end=\"1447\">mathematical methods / advanced calculus units</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr data-start=\"1451\" data-end=\"1454\" />\r\n\r\n<h3 data-section-id=\"1c1hc5w\" data-start=\"1456\" data-end=\"1478\">📦 Product Details</h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1479\" data-end=\"1650\">\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"ihttkt\" data-start=\"1479\" data-end=\"1503\">Author: Mary L. Boas</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1w0uoib\" data-start=\"1504\" data-end=\"1547\">Genre: Academic / Mathematics / Physics</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1b63gix\" data-start=\"1548\" data-end=\"1594\">Level: Undergraduate (2nd–3rd year mostly)</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"fh1ks1\" data-start=\"1595\" data-end=\"1628\">Format: Paperback / Hardcover</li>\r\n 	<li data-section-id=\"1lp14du\" data-start=\"1629\" data-end=\"1650\">Language: English</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Mathematical Methods in the Physical Sciences — Mary Boas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'mathematical-methods-in-the-physical-sciences-mary-boas', '', '', '2026-03-30 22:55:09', '2026-03-30 22:55:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bookshop/?post_type=product&#038;p=75', 0, 'product', '', 0),
